  <!-- ── Draw Oil ── -->
  <h2 id="draw-oil">Draw Oil Centrifuge Applications</h2>

  <p>
    Draw oil is a <strong>high-viscosity lubricant</strong> used in metal forming operations where wire, rod, or tube is pulled through a die to reduce its cross-section. Draw oil provides the extreme-pressure lubrication needed to prevent galling and tearing at the die-workpiece interface.
  </p>

  <p>
    Common draw oil applications include:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Aluminum Wire Drawing:</strong> Fine aluminum particles accumulate in draw oil as wire passes through progressive dies. Centrifuge purification prevents particle buildup that causes wire surface defects and die wear.</li>
    <li><strong>Copper and Brass Drawing:</strong> Copper fines are abrasive and accelerate die wear. Continuous centrifuge cleaning maintains draw oil quality and extends die life.</li>
    <li><strong>Tube Drawing:</strong> Both the inner mandrel and outer die generate metal fines that contaminate the draw oil. Centrifuge processing removes these particles to maintain surface quality.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Draw oils are typically high-viscosity fluids (40&ndash;80 cSt), which require higher centrifuge residence time for effective separation. Dolphin Centrifuge engineers size the centrifuge and adjust flow rates to account for the specific viscosity and temperature of each draw oil application.
  </p>

  <!-- ── Rolling Oil ── -->
  <h2 id="rolling-oil">Rolling Oil Centrifuge Applications</h2>

  <p>
    Rolling oil (also called rolling mill oil) is used in <strong>hot rolling and cold rolling</strong> operations where metal sheet, strip, or plate is passed between work rolls to reduce thickness. The rolling oil serves as both a lubricant and a coolant during the rolling process.
  </p>

  <h3>Hot Rolling Oil</h3>

  <p>
    In hot rolling operations, metal scale (iron oxide) breaks off the work surface and contaminates the rolling oil. A centrifuge removes this <strong>scale and metal debris</strong> continuously, preventing roll surface damage and product defects. Hot rolling oil centrifuges typically operate at elevated temperatures to maintain low viscosity for effective separation.
  </p>

  <h3>Cold Rolling Oil</h3>

  <p>
    Cold rolling operations generate fine metal particles that accumulate in the rolling oil and cause surface scratches and marks on the finished product. Centrifuge purification removes these sub-micron particles to maintain the high surface quality required for cold-rolled sheet and strip.
  </p>

  <h3>Rolling Oil Emulsions</h3>

  <p>
    Many rolling mills use oil-in-water emulsions rather than neat oil. A disc stack centrifuge can process these <strong>emulsion systems</strong>, removing metal fines and tramp oil while preserving the emulsion concentration. The centrifuge is configured for three-phase separation when both free water and solids must be removed from the rolling oil.
  </p>

  <!-- ── Materials ── -->
  <h2 id="materials">Materials of Construction</h2>

  <p>
    Cutting oil centrifuge components are built from materials selected for durability, corrosion resistance, and long service life in metalworking environments:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Centrifuge Bowl:</strong> 316L stainless steel &mdash; provides excellent corrosion resistance and mechanical strength at high rotational speeds</li>
    <li><strong>Distributor:</strong> Marine bronze &mdash; wear-resistant material for the oil distribution element inside the bowl</li>
    <li><strong>Bowl Covers:</strong> Silium (silicon-aluminum alloy) &mdash; lightweight, corrosion-resistant covers that reduce rotational inertia</li>
    <li><strong>Frame &amp; Base:</strong> Cast iron &mdash; heavy-duty construction for vibration dampening and long-term stability</li>
    <li><strong>Disc Stack:</strong> Stainless steel conical discs &mdash; precision-stamped for uniform spacing and maximum separation area</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These materials provide a service life of <strong>30+ years</strong> with proper maintenance. All wetted parts are corrosion-resistant and compatible with a wide range of cutting oil formulations and additive packages.
  </p>

